fields.Dialogue Text: "Apples."

fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm gonna *fuck* you for the rest of my LIFE, you understand?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "What is there to talk about? It's a racist world. I didn't make it that way. And neither did you -- and *you're* a racist too!"

fields.Dialogue Text: "Who is the lady driver? You won't get into trouble."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Like fuck you are. Why's your partner a multi-ethnic rainbow man? Why'd you not arrest Siileng? Fuck off, I ain't telling you shit."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "The man drops the near-finished cig..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The man drops the near-finished cigarette lingering between his fingers. He reaches for a new one, with a confident look.

fields.Title: You: ""What are you doing, Kim? Let me ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you doing, Kim? Let me handle it."

fields.Dialogue Text: "He did *something* -- he stole his employer's goods and another, honest lorryman's job. You know..." His smirk turns into a suspicious grin.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck, I oughtta..."

fields.Alternate1: "You're a Revacholian patriot? What's that all about?"

fields.Title: You: ""Limbo? What's going on here?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Limbo? What's going on here?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Welcome to Re..." The fat man stop..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Welcome to Re..." The fat man stops mid-sentence as he notices Lieutenant Kitsuragi.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Ye... no... never mind, officer. P..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ye... no... never mind, officer. Pleased to meet you. I'm a camionneur, a father of three, and a Revacholian patriot."

fields.Title: Shivers: "The wind howls over the Bay of Reva..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The wind howls over the Bay of Revachol -- a cascade of cold air, flowing through the tangled city streets.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Custom-made. Cost me a pretty penn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Custom-made. Cost me a pretty penny!" He rubs the back of his balding head.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""God damn right. They've been tryin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "God damn right. They've been trying to fuck us out of our heritage in the name of profits. But when they try to replace us they'll regret it."

fields.Title: Logic: "He doesn't live in Martinaise."
fields.Dialogue Text: He doesn't live in Martinaise.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "Lieutenant Kitsuragi's stern expres..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Lieutenant Kitsuragi's stern expression remains unchanged -- but you sense he can't be happy about this turn of events.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Fucking... homo cop." A globule of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fucking... homo cop." A globule of sweat gathers at his brow.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "The name resounds like a bell in th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The name resounds like a bell in the air -- a dark gong. You get a bad feeling about it.

fields.Title: Authority: "He's been expecting this. He's real..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's been expecting this. He's really puffed himself up.

fields.Title: You: ""Yekokataa is not in the south and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yekokataa is not in the south and they definitely don't grow apples there."

fields.Title: You: ""Apples then. From Graad. Right. Su..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Apples then. From Graad. Right. Sure."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""It's about... biological determini..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's about... biological determinism. Natural law. The sorting of the races." He spits on the ground.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""People who've studied these things..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "People who've studied these things say that we are superior by design. So, naturally, we Occidentals should be in charge. Obviously you can see the merits in that."
fields.Alternate1: "People who've studied these things say that *you* and *me* are superior by design." He glances at the lieutenant. "So, naturally, we Occidentals should be in charge. Obviously you can see the merits in that."

fields.Title: You: ""Uh, welcome, indeed. Who are you?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Uh, welcome, indeed. Who are you?"

fields.Title: You: ""You mean my partner, Lieutenant Ki..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You mean my partner, Lieutenant Kitsuragi?"

fields.Dialogue Text: On the bottom of the man's boots you see an intricate tangle of treads with no immediately discernible pattern.

fields.Dialogue Text: "It's Revachol!"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""The stench is getting unbearable."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The stench is getting unbearable." He turns to you. "Is there a reason you're bothering me?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Hello, compatriot!" He recognizes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hello, compatriot!" He recognizes you. "You have something to discuss?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "Lieutenant Kitsuragi's stern expres..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Lieutenant Kitsuragi's stern expression remains unchanged -- but you sense something there. Below...

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""What, aren't we *allowed* to say t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What, aren't we *allowed* to say that it's the kipts who do all the stealing around here? It's not *rotor science*, man..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant turns and gives you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant turns and gives you a barely perceptible nod.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Every school of thought and govern..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Every school of thought and government has failed in this city -- but I love it nonetheless. It belongs to me as much as it belongs to you."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Let's just go and ask Tommy, alrig..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's just go and ask Tommy, alright? We're wasting our time here."

fields.Title: You: ""You smell of booze and cigarettes,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You smell of booze and cigarettes, what's different about narcotics?"

fields.Title: Jump to: [Racist lorry driver: ""I don't know shit, and if I did I..."]
You: ""What kind of cargo are you suppose..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What kind of cargo are you supposed to pick up?"

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, how long has this been going..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, how long has this been going on then?"

fields.Title: You: ""I've been to your fucking lorry. I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I've been to your fucking lorry. I know where it is!" (Point to it.) "I'm gonna burn it down, you HEAR ME?!"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""A small 'Tempo' by the monument, g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A small 'Tempo' by the monument, green..." He turns to you. "Let's get into that lorry."

fields.Title: Half Light: "The main thing is to not overdo it...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The main thing is to not overdo it. Even when you're trying to scare someone, the most important thing is: how does it look on your resume?

fields.Title: You: ""Uh... your racism?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Uh... your racism?"

fields.Title: You: ""Damn it... I meant.. do you want t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn it... I meant.. do you want to find someplace private to... no, shit--"

fields.Title: You: ""So who does -- *you?*""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So who does -- *you?*"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "His eyes dart between you and the l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His eyes dart between you and the lieutenant. "I'm not scared of you -- or the mob. I'm under the protection of the Lorrymen and Carters Guild."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I'm not the only one. Look, I've r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not the only one. Look, I've read *books*," he gestures with his cigarette for emphasis. "The science of racial theory has all been proved, even if some people don't want to accept it."

fields.Title: Perception (Smell): "His physique reeks of heavy motor o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His physique reeks of heavy motor oils. His breath smells of high-tar content cigarettes. Probably *Astra Whites*.

fields.Title: You: ""You hiding smokes from me?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You hiding smokes from me?"

fields.Title: You: ""Well, I think we all learned somet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, I think we all learned something here." (Smile at the lorryman.)
fields.Alternate1: "I think we should all learn to respect each others opinions." (Betray your partner and smile at the lorryman in a conspiratorial manner.)

fields.Title: Logic: "No, it's Ruby running this ring lik..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, it's Ruby running this ring like Titus alluded to. But play along for now. Find out what everyone knows first. Siileng is your next lead.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm trying to turn back time. Can..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm trying to turn back time. Can you help me, brther?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Yeah, apples... I take it you had..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, apples... I take it you had other questions?"
fields.Alternate1: "Yeah, apples. I'm an apple-carter. I take it you had other questions?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Welcome to Revachol!" The lorry dr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Welcome to Revachol!" The lorry driver recognizes you. "Got rid of the other one, eh? Good call."

fields.Title: You: ""But...why?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "But...why?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""You two make a cute couple, you kn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You two make a cute couple, you know that?" The lorryman spits.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Just follow the smell. It smells l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just follow the smell. It smells like apricots and *oil* when you're nearby..." The lorryman lets out a raspy croak at his own sense of humour.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Yeah," he says, unsure where this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah," he says, unsure where this is leading. "They're his little bitches. He's got them all over the unions."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""You're not peones," he says. "You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're not peones," he says. "You wouldn't be investigating a drug-thing, if you were."

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah... maybe it *is*...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah... maybe it *is*..."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "There was a bunch of spilled boxes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There was a bunch of spilled boxes in the back of a big lorry nearby...

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Hell no. It's a *guild*. Invitatio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hell no. It's a *guild*. Invitation only. Unions work for the rich fucks. They're basically the same. Been trying to fuck us out of our heritage in the name of profits. But you can't replace experience."

fields.Title: You: ""Hello. Who are you?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hello. Who are you?"

fields.Title: You: ""Actually -- we do.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Actually -- we do."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I'm *not* in trouble right now --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm *not* in trouble right now -- and I don't have to tell you a single thing. Now fuck off."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Not sheep -- ostriches."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not sheep -- ostriches.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Actually, neither ostriches or shee..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Actually, neither ostriches or sheep bury their heads in the sand. It's just a saying.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Evidence of what? I haven't done a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Evidence of what? I haven't done anything." He puts out his cigarette and flicks the tiny stub toward the street.

fields.Title: You: ""Right. You're sure it's this *Siil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right. You're sure it's this *Siileng* and not, say, a *lady driver*?"

fields.Title: Composure: "He is comfortable reciting these th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He is comfortable reciting these thoughts. He's spent quite a lot of time meditating on the subject.

fields.Title: You: ""Hold on, what's a carter?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hold on, what's a carter?"

fields.Title: You: ""I know you've been giving me the r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know you've been giving me the run-around. Fess up, where's the lady driver?"

fields.Dialogue Text: The lorry driver glares at you intently, then shrugs. "Then I guess they grow apples somewhere else. You can never really tell with those Kojkos. They're *everywhere* -- except their own homes."

fields.Title: You: ""I did see one lorry with the trail..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I did see one lorry with the trailer doors open on my way here. Do you know what happened?"

fields.Title: You: ""So you *are* saying something.""

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "He eyes you warily, unsure how to r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He eyes you warily, unsure how to respond. This goes on for about two seconds, then...

fields.Title: You: ""You said something about the right..."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""The strike? They've been at it for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The strike? They've been at it for a while. A month, two months maybe?" He gestures towards the lorries. "But *this* here is just the last week or so."

fields.Title: You: ""You just look at people and make a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You just look at people and make arbitrary judgements."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Perhaps it's good to agree? To get..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Perhaps it's good to agree? To get him talking.

fields.Title: You: ""Where *exactly* is her lorry?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where *exactly* is her lorry?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""He did *something*. He stole his e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He did *something*. He stole his employer's goods and another, honest lorryman's job. Talk to him -- I don't know anything."
fields.Alternate1: "He did *something*. He stole his employer's goods and another lorryman's job. You should be thankful for the tip." He grins -- a wide smile.

fields.Title: Half Light: "*Change the topic* -- the way he sa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Change the topic* -- the way he says it makes it almost sound like a threat.

fields.Title: You: ""Shit.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shit."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Hey, if the name and description f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey, if the name and description fit by the very grace of nature, who am I to say otherwise?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Suit yourself, officer. Hide your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Suit yourself, officer. Hide your face in the sand if you so wish." He spits on the ground.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Oh?" The man seems mildly disappoi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh?" The man seems mildly disappointed that you don't want to hear more of his lecture.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""It's true." He pushes on. "Also, y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's true." He pushes on. "Also, you need to realize the dangers of *mixing races*. Who knows what might happen if people don't stay in their birthplace? You might end up with a new sub-race, with unknown characteristics, leading to extra competition. That's why you've got to *control* the offspring."

fields.Title: You: ""Cool, cool, cool. (Rub your hands..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cool, cool, cool. (Rub your hands together.) I changed my mind anyway."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I bet." His cool gaze pierces deep..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I bet." His cool gaze pierces deep, with noxious effluence wafting in the surrounding air.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "It's calling you out onto the field..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's calling you out onto the field! This man, *he's on your team*.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Hey man, you know. There are all s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey man, you know. There are all sorts of Invasions... " He looks at his boots, then you. "I thought we could rely on the cops. We're in this together, whether you realize it or not."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I don't know shit, and if I did I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know shit, and if I did I wouldn't tell you." He puffs on his cigarette.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Yeah, I drive a lorry. Back and fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, I drive a lorry. Back and forth. Sometimes I sit stuck in a traffic jam, guarding that lorry."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "There's your in. Take his side in t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's your in. Take his side in this particular fight.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Seriously, though, he's usually ju..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Seriously, though, he's usually just a little bit south of here. Down near the canal, you can't miss him. Just watch yourself..."
fields.Alternate1: "Looks like I offended your partner there." He doesn't look at the lieutenant. "Too bad. Siileng's usually a little bit south of here, near the canal. You can't miss him. Just watch yourselves..."

fields.Title: Authority: "Now it's not a big deal for him any..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Now it's not a big deal for him anymore. This is how he saves face.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: ""Apples" is exactly the kind of thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Apples" is exactly the kind of thing you'd say if you had something to hide...

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, sure, whatever. I'd really r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, sure, whatever. I'd really rather talk about something else."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Yeah, they're a big deal. My great..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, they're a big deal. My great-grandfather was a carter. Had a royal license and everything. We've tried to hold on to our privileges."

fields.Title: You: ""Why don't you and me step outside..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why don't you and me step outside for a little *talk*?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Oh yeah?" he snarls. "And what goo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh yeah?" he snarls. "And what goods are those?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""You're all bark and no bite. The r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're all bark and no bite. The real dogs are up in Jamrock. Everyone knows that."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""No I'm not. I'm not coming anywher..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No I'm not. I'm not coming anywhere -- and you're not taking me there. Now fuck off."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Sorry, all done." He puts out his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sorry, all done." He puts out his cigarette and flicks the tiny stub toward the street.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""This concerns you, policeman, so y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This concerns you, policeman, so you better be *vigilant*. The kipts are showing a good game lately, same with the mesquitos. And the other intruder species out there, breeding like rabbits. They're on the precipice of cultural victory."
fields.Alternate1: "This concerns you, policeman, so you better be *vigilant*. The damn kipts are showing up good lately, same with the mesquitos. And the other intruder species too." He throws a sharp glance at Lieutenant Kitsuragi. "They're on the precipice of cultural victory."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I salute you, compatriot. Defender..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I salute you, compatriot. Defenders of the Evening Lands have to stick together." He takes out a pack rolled up inside his sleeve. "Light up, brother. Ward off those jungle spirits."

fields.Title: Endurance: "Sure, sure, but that guy -- you wou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sure, sure, but that guy -- you wouldn't tell it by his looks, but he is *definitely* a brther and a kingsman. Ask if he knows how to turn back time!

fields.Title: You: ""That's no way to talk about an off..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's no way to talk about an officer of the law."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""For when the Invasion comes..." He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "For when the Invasion comes..." He glances at the lieutenant. "The last thing they'll see before the lights go out is *illustrious Revachol*."

fields.Title: You: ""So you're telling me that you don'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you're telling me that you don't know *anything* about drug smuggling through Terminal B?"

fields.Title: Half Light: "Men like this only respect two thin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Men like this only respect two things: strength and fear.

fields.Title: You: ""Hold on, but they make Al Gul -- a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hold on, but they make Al Gul -- alcohol -- in IIlmaraa too. I was told they do."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""They know they can't beat us in a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They know they can't beat us in a fair fight, so they have to get us to weaken ourselves somehow. It's racial sabotage. Racial *economic* sabotage."

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: You: ""Just tell me which one's her lorry!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just tell me which one's her lorry!"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""What?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""How about you fuck off? I ain't sa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How about you fuck off? I ain't saying *anything*."

fields.Title: You: ""Oh, so you drive a lorry?" (Preten..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, so you drive a lorry?" (Pretend you missed that last part.)

fields.Title: You: ""Listen, I agree. It's our responsi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Listen, I agree. It's our responsibility to keep this poison off the streets of Revachol, right?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Not at all! We're part of a guild..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not at all! We're part of a guild and everything... it's very ancient, very prestigious."

fields.Title: You: ""Who's that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who's that?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""He's the Samaran guy who likes to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's the Samaran guy who likes to pretend he's some kinda businessman... Really he's just selling his employer's stuff. Stuff he *stole* after he broke the seals on his Humanox lorry."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay, that's enough, detective. Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, that's enough, detective. That's enough."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "You can just make out a familiar pa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can just make out a familiar pattern in the intricate tangle of treads on the rubber of his soles. It is the map of your city!

fields.Title: Authority: "You *get* it."
fields.Dialogue Text: You *get* it.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Looks like the lieutenant has a pla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Looks like the lieutenant has a plan. Let him do this.

fields.Title: Composure: "Be careful. This man's still got so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Be careful. This man's still got some fight in him, by the looks of it. It won't be easy break him.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "The man bites his lip and drops the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The man bites his lip and drops the near-finished cigarette lingering between his fingers. He reaches for a new one.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I don't know, I don't even know he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know, I don't even know her name. She just rolls with the fleet and acts like a big shot. Some dyke probably. I haven't even seen her for days."

fields.Title: You: ""Look, I'm sorry, can you just tell..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, I'm sorry, can you just tell me what you know?"

fields.Title: You: ""What's a camionneur?" (Pretend you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's a camionneur?" (Pretend you missed that last part.)

fields.Title: You: ""To be honest, I can't really remem..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "To be honest, I can't really remember what that means. Please explain."

fields.Title: You: ""Right. I've already made up my min..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right. I've already made up my mind. Wanna hear it?" (Jump ahead.)

fields.Title: Endurance: "Remember, brther, you say the hard..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Remember, brther, you say the hard things -- the gd things. Most folk haven't got the stomach for it.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Why would you tell a *brther* off..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why would you tell a *brther* off like that? He *clearly* knows things! Probably knows how to turn back time too. Try to get back on his good side.

fields.Title: You: ""What's a... *Revachol*?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's a... *Revachol*?"
fields.Alternate1: "Hey, I know Revachol! That's where we are."

fields.Title: Empathy: "You sense slight embarrassment for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You sense slight embarrassment for the outburst. Or is it pride? Impossible to tell.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Been admiring the stompers, eh?" H..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Been admiring the stompers, eh?" He grins. "Sure thing, check 'em out." He lifts his left foot, then the right.
fields.Alternate1: "Been admiring the stompers, runt?" He grins. "Sure, I can *demonstrate* them." He lifts up to show you his left foot, then the right.

fields.Title: You: ""Show me her lorry right *fucking*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Show me her lorry right *fucking* now. The lady driver's lorry -- WHERE IS IT?!"
fields.Sequence: HideActualHeld(); PlayAnimation(Racist, grabStart); PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, grabStart);

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant tries to remain impa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant tries to remain impassive but the slight arch of his eyebrow tells you that he's liking it.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "He takes a long suck on his cigaret..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He takes a long suck on his cigarette, appearing to savour the taste. "Since he left I haven't had anyone to talk to..."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Of course he's a lorry driver! Wha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course he's a lorry driver! What -- he tell you he's just some simple businessman or some shit? He's selling his employer's stuff after he broke the seals on his Humanox lorry."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""His tribe are natural liars. It's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "His tribe are natural liars. It's in their blood..." He nods in a sagely manner, then another puff of that cigarette: "He's your man, alright. One-hundred percent."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Nah. You wouldn't just leave him o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah. You wouldn't just leave him out there if you..." He tries to light a fresh cigarette, but his hands are shaking now. The sentence simply ends.

fields.Title: You: ""I don't really know where that cam..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't really know where that came from..."

fields.Title: Empathy: "Looks like you got his adrenaline u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Looks like you got his adrenaline up too.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's not a hard job. It won't take..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's not a hard job. It won't take a long time. It won't make Padre Madre *angry*." He looks at him. "But a stupid fucking racist is standing in the way, *protecting* this fucking thief..."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I don't think you're as *down* wit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't think you're as *down* with our fight as you'd like me to believe, *brother*. Why's the saffron-man still there? Talk to him -- I don't know anything."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Not the most popular topic nowaday..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not the most popular topic nowadays, with the Coalition in charge and all. You might want to *change the topic* -- that is, bury your head under the sand like common sheep."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Just the truth." The man shrugs. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just the truth." The man shrugs. "I'm a truth-teller, above all else."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Yup, it's one of their main export..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yup, it's one of their main exports. They grow 'em down south Yekokataa. A beautiful place, got great scenic vistas."

fields.Title: You: ""It's literally in the name: *Zone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's literally in the name: *Zone of Ecological Catastrophe*."

fields.Title: You: ""If you all were at the Whirling, h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If you all were at the Whirling, how do you know it was *kipts* who broke into the lorry?"

fields.Title: You: ""Bad for him, I guess.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Bad for him, I guess."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, what else have you thought u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, what else have you thought up?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Open your eyes. Haven't you notice..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Open your eyes. Haven't you noticed something different lately? An unfortunate downturn, maybe? When members of the superior race cease to believe in their innate superiority, they stop competing for resources."

fields.Title: You: ""Right. You're sure it's him and no..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right. You're sure it's him and not, say, a *lady driver*?"

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Your partner needs backup. Now's yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your partner needs backup. Now's your moment to shine!

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "Silence. The air between them becom..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Silence. The air between them becomes tense.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Do continue, *sir*." The lieutenan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do continue, *sir*." The lieutenant steps up to him again, his frame tense as a coiled spring.

You: ""Is that... a map of Revachol?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is that... a map of Revachol?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Not in, not out. I'll never betray..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not in, not out. I'll never betray the purity of my tribe."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Whatever you say, *officers*." He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Whatever you say, *officers*." He waits impassively, cigarette smouldering between his fingers.

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, the street vendor south of h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, the street vendor south of here? That guy's a lorry driver?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Guess so." He grins, contented wit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Guess so." He grins, contented with himself.

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: You: ""That's a map of Revachol.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's a map of Revachol."

fields.Title: Authority: "You could ask him to show you the s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You could ask him to show you the soles of his boots. He definitely looks like someone capable of a lynching. Maybe he was present?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I know exactly what you meant. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know exactly what you meant. You think my *kind* doesn't belong here. That I should *watch myself* and *behave*."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Go right ahead." The man scratches..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Go right ahead." The man scratches his heavyset stomach. "You may be a cop, but that won't help you avoid the calamity to come."

fields.Title: You: ""We're done for now." [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "We're done for now." [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah, I'm *not* down with this --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, I'm *not* down with this -- why don't you go fuck yourself?"

fields.Title: Half Light: "Why are you even trying? There is n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why are you even trying? There is no way to work yourself into a rage without it looking *bad*. And you look bad enough without this *nasty* business.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "The lorryman raises an eyebrow. "Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lorryman raises an eyebrow. "This some kind of homo thing?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "For a moment the lorryman is silent..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For a moment the lorryman is silent. Then he spits on the pavement. "Yeah, him."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "He's got a smoke right there, in hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's got a smoke right there, in his fucking hand! Snatch that shit out of his fat fingers! You need it after listening to his garbage.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Can't have it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Can't have it."

fields.Title: You: ""Can I get a drag of that then?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Can I get a drag of that then?"

fields.Title: You: ""On second thought, let's talk abou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "On second thought, let's talk about something else."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Race is a simplistic means of socia..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Race is a simplistic means of social classification based on easily observed attributes, hunches and pseudo-science.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""C'mon, man, the holler... It's jus..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "C'mon, man, the holler... It's just a greeting. A lorry driver thing."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I ain't saying nothing.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I ain't saying nothing."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "He stares at the Yellow Man mug, th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He stares at the Yellow Man mug, then suddenly... he explodes: "HAHAHA! HAHAHA! Oh man! Oh... man, that's great. Look at that guy go. Haven't seen anything that funny in a while."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Look, ace detective, I come from a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, ace detective, I come from a long line of lorrymen. We got ancient rights and privileges..." He loses his patience for explaining it.

fields.Title: Logic: "If they were getting drunk inside t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If they were getting drunk inside the Whirling-in-Rags how could they know who broke into the lorry?

fields.Title: Half Light: "Stop now. Just ask the other driver..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stop now. Just ask the other drivers. You have to find out who the lady driver is and you can't do it like this. It's too much.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""That's the one, brother. His tribe..."

fields.Title: Empathy: "Oh no, not *too* happy."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh no, not *too* happy.

fields.Title: You: ""Fair enough. I got some other ques..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fair enough. I got some other questions."

fields.Title: You: ""Fuckin' A, Kim. I've got your back..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuckin' A, Kim. I've got your back." (Give the lieutenant a punch on the shoulder.)
fields.Alternate1: "Fuckin' A, Kim. I've got your back!" (Point your finger pistols at the lieutenant.)

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Did you miss the part where I said..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Did you miss the part where I said they aren't here yet? Besides, even if I did have some I wouldn't go putting my nose in them..." He looks at you with a strange glint in his eyes.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Sure fucking is! We have a guild a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure fucking is! We have a guild and everything... very ancient, very prestigious."

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, I can really tell you're a pr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, I can really tell you're a prime example of superior design."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay... and?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay... and?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "What's up with your soles?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, yes. *Where* is he?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "You've seen that corpse in the ceramic armour there?" The lieutenant points to the yard. "Did his shitty little guild protect *him*?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "C'mon, man, I just said 'Welcome to Revachol'... It's a lorry driver thing."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Sounds like a cover story to me."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""So, lately we Occidentals have exp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So, lately we Occidentals have experienced an unfortunate downturn: when members of the superior race cease to believe in their innate superiority, they stop competing for resources."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""*When* did she go away?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "*When* did she go away?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""A lorry driver. Who drives a lorry..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A lorry driver. Who drives a lorry. Or is sometimes stuck in traffic jams, guarding that lorry."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Sorry I couldn't be of any help."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sorry I couldn't be of any help." He gives you an ambivalently mocking half-nod.

fields.Title: You: ""Oh, so you're just a racist. Makes..."

fields.Title: You: ""He's right. You're undermining our..."

fields.Title: Authority: "What happened? Did your balls shriv..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What happened? Did your balls shrivel up? You had plenty of chances to get off this road, but no, you let this guy keep talking. Then when the time came to make your choice you tried to split the difference. Weak.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "He's given you the run-around. Let'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's given you the run-around. Let's be honest, you were *bested*.

fields.Title: You: ""If it's not you, then who's runnin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If it's not you, then who's running drugs through Terminal B?"

fields.Title: You: ""Oh, alright then.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, alright then."

fields.Title: You: ""Guess I need to pay him a visit, t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Guess I need to pay him a visit, then."

fields.Title: Authority: "You could push him by asking him to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You could push him by asking him to show you the soles of his boots. He definitely looks like someone capable of a lynching.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""You know where that shit comes fro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You know where that shit comes from? Saramiriza, Safre, Iilmaraa. They take the money from our local junkies here and then use it to out-compete us in the manufacturing sector."

fields.Title: You: "(Look at the sole.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: (Look at the sole.)

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""The problem? The damn kipts are sh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The problem? The damn kipts are showing a real good game lately! Same with the mesquitos. And all the other intruder species out there, breeding like rabbits. They're on the precipice of cultural victory."
fields.Alternate1: "The problem? The damn kipts are showing a real good game lately, same with the mesquitos." He throws a sharp glance at Lieutenant Kitsuragi. "And the other intruder species too. They're on the precipice of cultural victory."

fields.Title: You: ""What's your name, fuckhead?! I'm g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's your name, fuckhead?! I'm gonna go on police radio sayin' this guy told Madre to FUCK OFF."

fields.Title: Half Light: "Failing the last time was so demora..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Failing the last time was so demoralizing and *puzzling* that you just can't work up the rage anymore.

fields.Title: You: ""Got a smoke?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Got a smoke?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "In fact, Yekokataa is a desolate wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In fact, Yekokataa is a desolate wasteland whose name literally translates to *Zone of Ecological Catastrophe*. It features no scenic vistas and supports virtually no plant or animal life.

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Aces! Good to know the law's got o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Aces! Good to know the law's got our backs." He gives a quick two-finger salute. "For Revachol, the Suzerain! The world is our Suzerainty."

fields.Title: Logic: "No, it's Ruby running this ring lik..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, it's Ruby running this ring like Titus alluded to. But play along for now. Find out what everyone knows first. Siileng is your next lead.

fields.Title: Authority: "The lieutenant's impassive mask has..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant's impassive mask has been replaced with intensity. He speaks not as a cop, but as a citizen. He is *Vacholiere*. A Revacholian.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, so it's an ethnic slur."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""'Cause that's what they're all cal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "'Cause that's what they're all called. Kojko Pitjic, Lzloslaw Kojko. Kojkowicz Someone. Low self-esteem those guys have. Mind you, they look Occidental, but they're not... *really* like us."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "He laughs. Nervously. "Sure I'm sur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He laughs. Nervously. "Sure I'm sure," he says. "His tribe are natural liars. It's in their blood..."

fields.Title: You: ""Never mind, let's keep moving." [L..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Never mind, let's keep moving." [Leave.]

fields.Title: Empathy: "Usually he says it with derision, b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Usually he says it with derision, but to you he seems to say it as an actual greeting.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Cultural victory? What is this then..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Cultural victory? What is this then?

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""It sure is!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It sure is!"

fields.Title: You: ""Where did you get boots like that?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where did you get boots like that?"

fields.Title: You: ""You do understand you're *stomping..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You do understand you're *stomping on Revachol* every day, don't you?"

fields.Title: You: ""So, I take it you're *not* smuggli..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So, I take it you're *not* smuggling drugs out of Martinaise?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No." The lieutenant turns to the l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No." The lieutenant turns to the lorryman. "He means *La Puta Madre*."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No. Of course not. *We're* not peo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. Of course not. *We're* not peones. But *if* we were... and one of Madre's drivers were to be stealing from him -- then it's a good peone's job to find out who that is."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant raises one eyebrow...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant raises one eyebrow. "You've seen the corpse in the yard, yes? You took a peek. I *know* you did. Does it look like his friends protected *him*?"

fields.Title: You: ""Is it yours?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is it yours?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""It's what the kipts of Boogie Stre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's what the kipts of Boogie Street are going for -- right under our noses. And the others too, on the radio. Heard any *chansons* lately? Heard any *mottettos* or *lieder*? No. Dominating culture is how they plan to win. They say so themselves."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Nope nothing. You're sure it's okay..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nope nothing. You're sure it's okay. You wriggled your way out of a tight one there. Didn't tell him to fuck off, *or* join his cause. Well done.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "What he means is: fixation on the R..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What he means is: fixation on the Revacholian *nation* makes it harder for Revachol to actually attain self-determination.

fields.Title: Half Light: "There! His voice grows smaller, as..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There! His voice grows smaller, as yours...

fields.Title: You: ""*When* did she go away?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "*When* did she go away?"

fields.Title: You: ""The jig's up. I've got the goods o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The jig's up. I've got the goods on you."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Or you could look around, find this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Or you could look around, find this guy's cabin. Check all the lorries. It's scary when cops are snooping in your things, no?

fields.Title: You: ""Just tell me who the god damn lady..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Just tell me who the god damn lady driver is!"

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, but why the word 'Kojko'?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, but why the word 'Kojko'?"

fields.Title: Endurance: "But this guy does. He's a bulwark,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But this guy does. He's a bulwark, a Defender of the Evening Lands. He may know how to turn back time...

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Someone with a cart, what did you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Someone with a cart, what did you think it was? That's how deep into history our thing reaches -- before machines."

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "'Kojko' may be another derogative...."
fields.Dialogue Text: 'Kojko' may be another derogative. For a person from Graad, you think.

fields.Title: You: ""Actually, I'm not that interested..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Actually, I'm not that interested in your cargo."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Racist lorry driver: "The man bites his lip and drops the..."]
Tutorial Agent: "CIGARETTES are a TOOL. Equip them i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: CIGARETTES are a TOOL. Equip them in your HELD slot in your INVENTORY.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "Damn. It didn't work. You should ha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Damn. It didn't work. You should have signalled you're a nationalist before.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "If this guy's all the *Occidentals*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If this guy's all the *Occidentals* have, well... let's just say he's not exactly ripped.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Oh, I'm just a simple camionneur,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, I'm just a simple camionneur, a father of three, and a Revachol patriot."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "And, of course, what *social sensib..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And, of course, what *social sensibilities* you're bringing to the table. Remain sensitive. People are watching.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Make me, runt." He blows a cloud o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Make me, runt." He blows a cloud of smoke right in front of your face.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "A legendary -- and not in a *good*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A legendary -- and not in a *good* way -- crime boss from Jamrock. Controls what is probably the most powerful organised crime outfit in Revachol West.

fields.Title: You: ""Sheep don't bury their heads, ostr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sheep don't bury their heads, ostriches do. You mixed up your metaphors."

fields.Title: You: ""Nothing worthwhile here." [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing worthwhile here." [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""So. Can I see the apples?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So. Can I see the apples?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "The man shakes his head, dismayed -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The man shakes his head, dismayed -- furiously pulling on his cigarette: "It's a fuckin' travesty, is what it is."

fields.Title: Endurance: "A sudden vibration passes through y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A sudden vibration passes through your small intestine. Like a buzzer.

fields.Title: You: ""Oh, so we're *in* Revachol.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, so we're *in* Revachol."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I don't go for that foreign piss...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't go for that foreign piss. Proper booze is made in Mundi, or sometimes I like a dram of that Yugo-Graad vodka. Kojko's ain't worth much, but they do know booze."

fields.Title: You: ""The one re-selling humanitarian ai..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The one re-selling humanitarian aid packages, right?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""That's the one. His tribe are natu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's the one. His tribe are natural liars. It's in their blood..." The lorryman takes a slow, satisfied drag and blows a smoke ring.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""He's your man, alright. One-hundre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's your man, alright. One-hundred percent. He's a lorryman selling his employer's stuff -- broke the seals on his Humanox lorry. No doubt he's selling drugs too."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""So you're telling us that you don'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you're telling us that you don't know *anything* about drug smuggling through Terminal B?"

fields.Title: You: ""I *knew* there was something off a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I *knew* there was something off about that guy."

fields.Title: You: ""So it's a kind of union?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So it's a kind of union?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Technically, you're *stomping* on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Technically, you're *stomping* on Revachol every step you take."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Welcome to Revachol!" announces th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Welcome to Revachol!" announces the rotund man. The remark isn't addressed to you. Its addressed to the lieutenant.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Fine." He shrugs."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fine." He shrugs.

fields.Title: You: ""And that's a privilege?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "And that's a privilege?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Good. If we, the Evening People, p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good. If we, the Evening People, pull together -- we can form a bulwark against these troubled times!" The man grins at you. "Root out the forces that seek to undermine the well-being of our people."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Look, fuck you, man!" He tries to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, fuck you, man!" He tries to wave you off. "It's some lorry down there, green banged up thing. I don't fucking *know* who she is."

fields.Title: You: ""So who does -- the lady driver?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So who does -- the lady driver?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""What? Here on the street? You won'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What? Here on the street? You won't." He shakes his head. "Now fuck off."

fields.Title: You: ""First. You *knew* Siileng didn't d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "First. You *knew* Siileng didn't do it."

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["TASK.probe_drivers_about_drugs"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.probe_drivers_about_drugs_done"] == false  and   Variable["TASK.who_is_the_ladydriver"] == true

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""That's too bad. It's all done for...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's too bad. It's all done for." He puts out his cigarette and flicks the tiny stub toward the street.

fields.Title: You: ""You tell him.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You tell him."

fields.Title: You: ""Apples?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Apples?"
fields.Alternate1: "One says it's apples, the other diamonds -- c'mon, what are you *really* hauling?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Yes, sir." He gives you a tiny moc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, sir." He gives you a tiny mock salute. "Pleased to meet you, officer. I'm a camionneur, a father of three, and a Revacholian patriot."

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah, alright. I wasn't really tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, alright. I wasn't really that interested in your cargo anyway."

fields.Title: Half Light: "Stop now. Just go away, ask that To..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stop now. Just go away, ask that Tommy or something. You have to find out who she is and you can't do it like this. It's too much.

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, I don't want to deal with th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, I don't want to deal with this." [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""That's all I needed to know. Now l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's all I needed to know. Now let me ask you something else."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Then I presume you're familiar wit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then I presume you're familiar with his *peones*?"

fields.Title: Drama: "The lieutenant adopts a rodentine q..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant adopts a rodentine quality. Be cool, sire. He's getting *into* this.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Listen up, fuckwit. You don't scar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Listen up, fuckwit. You don't scare me. You cops don't run Revachol West. You don't run Martinaise. You don't run shit."
fields.Alternate1: "Listen up, fuckwits. You don't scare me. You cops don't run Revachol West. You don't run Martinaise. You don't run anything."
fields.Alternate2: "Listen up, fuckwit. You don't scare me. You cops don't run Revachol West. You don't run Martinaise. You don't run anything. You're useless."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "He smirks. "I don't know what you'r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He smirks. "I don't know what you're talking about."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Welcome to Revachol!" the rotund m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Welcome to Revachol!" the rotund man announces. He has a lit cigarette between his fingers.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Not much anymore. I'm here to pick..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not much anymore. I'm here to pick up some cargo, but the dockworkers are on strike, so... it's a sit-and-wait-on-your-ass situation."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Looking for something?" The lorry..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looking for something?" The lorry driver recognizes you.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It's men like you who keep Revacho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's men like you who keep Revachol divided, making it that much harder for everyone to climb out of this post-war limbo."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm gonna put you in a cell with a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm gonna put you in a cell with a giant kipt. You're gonna be bleeding kipt dick, you hear me?"

fields.Title: You: ""You know... your *goods*.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You know... your *goods*."

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: You: ""What's happening? You sound angry,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's happening? You sound angry, Kim."

fields.Title: You: ""You keep saying 'Kojkos'. What doe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You keep saying 'Kojkos'. What does that actually mean?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Yeah? Says who?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah? Says who?"

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, what's this *cultural victor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, what's this *cultural victory*?"

fields.Title: You: ""You're lorryman, right? What's you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're lorryman, right? What's your stance on drugs?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""What do you think? I can't leave t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you think? I can't leave the lorry unguarded. Stuff's been getting looted lately. It's those little kipts sneaking around at night... If they touch my stuff, the bosses will be on my ass like ass cancer."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Isn't it obvious? Fuckin' Siileng,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Isn't it obvious? Fuckin' Siileng, that beady-eyed South-Samaran." He spits on the ground. "His little side business is a scam. I wouldn't be surprised if he was peddling drugs as well."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Isn't saying nothing saying somethi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Isn't saying nothing saying something, or did I just *blow your mind*?

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "I've softened him up. As best as I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I've softened him up. As best as I could. Now it's on you to finish the job.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Don't you *Welcome to Revachol* me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't you *Welcome to Revachol* me," the lieutenant fires back. "My grandfather came here from a three-thousand-year-old racist-isolationist culture, while your ancestors came to this island a mere three hundred years ago."

fields.Title: You: ""Stop ripping into this guy. He's j..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Stop ripping into this guy. He's just really proud of being Revacholian."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Relax. You've got all you can get h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Relax. You've got all you can get here. He probably doesn't even *know* what he's hauling -- even if it *is* something unsavoury. So he'd remain unaccountable.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Whoah, jackpot. *Racist* jackpot!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Whoah, jackpot. *Racist* jackpot!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I wouldn't be so sure about it --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I wouldn't be so sure about it -- not until we've heard what Siileng himself has to say."

fields.Title: You: ""So you're in a carter's guild?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So you're in a carter's guild?"

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Heh." A condescending chortle. "I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Heh." A condescending chortle. "I knew you people don't understand *poetry*."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""What?" The lorryman erupts in cont..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What?" The lorryman erupts in contemptuous laughter. "What do you think we're doing right now, runt? We're outside, talking!"

fields.Title: Jump to: [Racist lorry driver: ""Make me, runt." He blows a cloud o..."]
Racist lorry driver: ""Why would I do that? I am an hones..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why would I do that? I am an honest man." He puts out his cigarette and flicks the tiny stub toward the street.

fields.Title: You: ""Hand it over. I'm confiscating it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hand it over. I'm confiscating it as evidence."

fields.Title: You: ""But I really need it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "But I really need it."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Apples." He puts out his cigarette..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Apples." He puts out his cigarette and flicks the stub across the street.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant exhales and resumes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant exhales and resumes his regular calmness.

fields.Title: You: ""Serves him right.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Serves him right."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I'm not *just* racist. Look, I've..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not *just* racist. Look, I've read *books*," he gestures with his cigarette for emphasis. "The science of racial theory has all been proved, even if some people don't want to accept it."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: "He laughs. Nervously. "No, it's, uh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He laughs. Nervously. "No, it's, uh -- you know, the Samaran guy who likes to pretend he's some kinda businessman? He's just selling his employer's stuff. Stuff he *stole* after he broke the seals on his Humanox lorry."

fields.Title: You: ""Welcome to Revachol. I like it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Welcome to Revachol. I like it."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""You'll see when the time comes, of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You'll see when the time comes, officer," he grins and caresses the side of his boot. "*True* patriots carry Revachol in their very soles."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Drugs? They're shit, man. I don't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Drugs? They're shit, man. I don't let anything pollute my body." He takes a long drag on his cigarette.

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""I've told you everything I've got...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I've told you everything I've got." He looks around nervously. "Can you please stop talking to me now?"

fields.Title: You: ""Where do I find him?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Where do I find him?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Not just the unions. He has peones..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not just the unions. He has peones *everywhere*. Some say he even has them in the RCM." He gets closer to him. "Dirty fucking peones who'd do *anything* for him. Multi-ethnic drug addicts..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant looks at you. "How d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant looks at you. "How do you want to proceed?"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "This man looks like trouble. You mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This man looks like trouble. You might not want to get into this right *now*. Plenty of time later...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He pays you no attention. "It's men..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He pays you no attention. "It's men like you who keep Revachol divided, making it that much harder for everyone to climb out of this post-war limbo."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant turns to the lorryma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant turns to the lorryman. "You mean *La Puta Madre*."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""No.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""It's my last one.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's my last one."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""He means the people living in Graa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He means the people living in Graad."

fields.Title: Racist lorry driver: ""Trusting street thugs with their g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Trusting street thugs with their goods is going to fuck 'em right up the ass, mark my words. Generations of practice ain't no laughing matter."

fields.Title: You: ""Why are you addressing my partner..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why are you addressing my partner like that?"

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Not a lot of moral fibre on this on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not a lot of moral fibre on this one yet, he thinks. Wriggled out of it.

fields.Title: Shivers: "The wind howls over the Bay of Reva..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The wind howls over the Bay of Revachol -- a cascade of cold air, flowing through the city streets. Those same streets have left their share of scuff marks on the underside of your green snakeskin shoes.

fields.Title: You: ""Why not?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why not?"

fields.Title: You: ""It's a double negative. Not saying..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's a double negative. Not saying nothing means you're saying something."

fields.Title: You: ""Now that that's settled, we have a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Now that that's settled, we have a couple of questions."

fields.Title: You: ""So... he was a garbage man?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "So... he was a garbage man?"
